# Design direction

UI work should support a **premium wellness / medical aesthetics** brand: calm, luxurious, and trustworthy.

## Goals

- Clean layouts with clear hierarchy
- Confident typography (serif headlines, readable sans body)
- Generous spacing and balanced composition
- Motion that feels **smooth and intentional**, not gimmicky
- Refined hover and focus states; accessible contrast on cream backgrounds

## Brand palette

- Primary accent: **ARC teal** (see CSS variables in `src/app/globals.css`)
- Surfaces: **cream / white** with subtle separation (borders, soft shadows) where helpful
- Text: **charcoal** on light backgrounds; ensure legibility on photography overlays

## Sections

- Keep card grids and CTAs **consistent** with existing patterns unless asymmetry is deliberate
- Photography should feel **elevated and relevant** (wellness, care, environment)—swap placeholders when production assets exist
- Avoid clutter, heavy outlines, or random accent colors

## Motion

- Respect **`prefers-reduced-motion`**: simpler or static fallbacks where motion is decorative
- Hero scroll interactions must not trap keyboard-only users; preserve accessible focus order

## Responsive quality

Responsive behavior is part of design quality. Follow `responsive-mobile-first.mdc`.
